And you've worked with some of the most legendary artists like ever.

01:09:15.080 --> 01:09:15.500
Yeah, man.

01:09:15.600 --> 01:09:15.680
Yeah.

01:09:15.680 --> 01:09:23.840
I mean, one of the guys I feel like you're just probably friends first and then collaborators second is Thundercat, who I saw you live with in New York.

01:09:23.880 --> 01:09:24.440
Yeah, yeah.

01:09:24.440 --> 01:09:26.340
Um, he's amazing, man.

01:09:26.340 --> 01:09:27.140
He's so awesome.

01:09:27.140 --> 01:09:34.120
And he, he credits you for having helped give him a voice and cause he was just playing bass primarily.

01:09:34.120 --> 01:09:34.520
Right.

01:09:34.520 --> 01:09:39.160
And you kind of helped him out and you were like, look, man, you should just sing over your, over your tracks.

01:09:39.160 --> 01:09:39.720
Is that right?

01:09:39.720 --> 01:09:40.000
Yeah.

01:09:40.060 --> 01:09:44.760
