01:09:44.920 --> 01:09:46.140
You know, let's do it.

01:09:46.300 --> 01:09:48.980
And, and then there was one day I'll never forget.

01:09:49.180 --> 01:09:50.820
And I think about it all the time.

01:09:51.020 --> 01:09:54.820
We were sitting in my apartment, my sweaty apartment in Northridge.

01:09:54.820 --> 01:09:58.800
Um, and he just, you know, we were working on some music.

01:09:58.920 --> 01:10:02.500
I had these like, like portable, portable lunch tables.

01:10:02.700 --> 01:10:07.400
They're like, they're like, uh, you know, the classic picnic tables or whatever.

01:10:07.500 --> 01:10:09.740
That's what I had all my, my gear set up on.

01:10:09.740 --> 01:10:13.140
And it was like surrounded by all these like medicinal marijuana jars.

01:10:14.740 --> 01:10:19.900
And it was, yeah, he just looks over at me and he was like, man, I want to be your artist.

01:10:21.540 --> 01:10:26.320
And I, I was like, yeah, what does that even mean?

01:10:26.320 --> 01:10:26.900
You know what I mean?

01:10:26.900 --> 01:10:27.860
Like, what does that even mean?

01:10:27.900 --> 01:10:31.120
I've never, I've never done that sort of thing before.

01:10:31.980 --> 01:10:36.760
And, um, yeah, we've just been going at it, man, ever since we've just been going for it.

01:10:36.760 --> 01:10:38.560
And it's, it's been awesome to see.

01:10:38.720 --> 01:10:50.720
And, and honestly, something that I take so much pride in aside from my own work is, you know, just seeing how his music and his message and his influences affected the world.

01:10:50.720 --> 01:10:51.040
Yeah.

01:10:51.640 --> 01:11:01.840
You see, he's another guy who like, you know, back in the day, I think was always respected, like as a, almost like an artist, artist where it was like, he's amazing on the bass.

01:11:01.960 --> 01:11:02.080
Yeah.

01:11:02.080 --> 01:11:09.260
